XML parsing is extremely dangerous when handling untrusted input because of XML External Entity (XXE) attacks. The most insidious variant is Blind XXE with Out-of-Band (OOB) data exfiltration, where attackers can steal data even when they don't see the parsed output directly.

**VULNERABLE CODE**:

```csharp
